  <header id="home">
    <h1>Food Gardening in South Africa</h1>
    <p>Growing your own food for a sustainable and healthy future</p>
  </header>

  <section class="intro">
    <img class="main-image" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1598030374762-5c92d3ef5638" alt="Fresh vegetable garden with leafy greens">
    <img class="icon" src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/3075/3075977.png" alt="Leaf icon">
    <h2>What is Food Gardening?</h2>
    <p>
      Food gardening focuses on growing edible plants such as vegetables, fruits, and herbs. It promotes food security,
      self-sufficiency, and sustainability by allowing families to grow their own produce while reducing food expenses
      and improving nutrition.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="challenges" class="challenges">
    <img class="main-image" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600377915240-8b2d9d89b27c" alt="Dry backyard soil representing lack of land and water">
    <img class="icon" src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/2169/2169874.png" alt="Warning icon">
    <h2>Challenges of Backyard Gardening in South Africa</h2>
    <p>
      One major challenge is limited access to land, especially in urban areas where space is scarce and costly. Water
      scarcity also affects many households, particularly in informal settlements. These challenges make it hard to
      maintain backyard gardens and grow enough food for families.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="solutions" class="solutions">
    <img class="main-image" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1603575448360-abb34f5c0c2a" alt="Rainwater harvesting system and drip irrigation setup">
    <img class="icon" src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/706/706164.png" alt="Water drop icon">
    <h2>Solutions to Gardening Challenges</h2>
    <p>
      Addressing these issues involves promoting equitable land access and community gardens. Investing in rainwater
      harvesting and water-saving irrigation methods like drip systems helps overcome water shortages and supports
      sustainable gardening practices.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="tools" class="tools">
    <img class="main-image" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1598030374762-f6c4b95e3f92" alt="Gardening tools like spades, trowels, and watering cans">
    <img class="icon" src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/3069/3069114.png" alt="Tools icon">
    <h2>Tools for Food Gardening</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Basic Hand Tools:</strong> Spades, shovels, and trowels for digging and planting.</li>
      <li><strong>Pruning Tools:</strong> Shears and clippers for trimming and harvesting.</li>
      <li><strong>Watering Equipment:</strong> Garden hoses, watering cans, and drip irrigation systems.</li>
      <li><strong>Monitoring Tools:</strong> Soil moisture sensors, pH meters, and thermometers for better crop management.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="tips" class="tips">
    <img class="main-image" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1592928305337-0c730bbf1c5e" alt="Healthy vegetable garden thriving">
    <img class="icon" src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/414/414974.png" alt="Tips icon">
    <h2>How to Achieve a Well-Performing Garden</h2>
    <p>
      To have a productive and healthy garden, follow these key practices:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Choose the Right Plants:</strong> Select crops suited to your climate, soil, and available sunlight.</li>
      <li><strong>Soil Preparation:</strong> Enrich the soil with compost or organic matter to ensure nutrients are abundant.</li>
      <li><strong>Water Wisely:</strong> Use drip irrigation or watering cans to provide consistent moisture without overwatering.</li>
      <li><strong>Regular Maintenance:</strong> Prune, weed, and monitor for pests regularly to keep plants healthy.</li>
      <li><strong>Rotate Crops:</strong> Avoid planting the same crops in the same spot each season to prevent nutrient depletion and pests.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>By following these steps, your garden can thrive, providing fresh and nutritious produce consistently.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="conclusion" class="conclusion">
    <img class="main-image" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1606761568499-6b9e4082a4f1" alt="Beautiful community vegetable garden">
    <img class="icon" src="https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/616/616408.png" alt="Plant icon">
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
      Backyard and community gardening can transform how South Africans approach food production. By improving land
      access and water management, and encouraging collaboration, food gardening can build resilience, fight poverty,
      and promote a sustainable, greener nation.
    </p>
  </section>

